From: Craig Miller <craig@nextidea.io>
Date: 2026-06-22
Subject: [PATCH] Runtime: use 16KB SWIFT_PAGE_SIZE on aarch64 Linux

The Swift runtime's backtrace machinery allocates static buffers
aligned to SWIFT_PAGE_SIZE and protects them with mprotect(). On a
kernel built with CONFIG_ARM64_16K_PAGES=y (Asahi-Linux on Apple
Silicon, Raspberry Pi OS 64-bit, RHEL 9 arm64), the kernel requires
mprotect() addresses to be 16KB-aligned, but SWIFT_PAGE_SIZE evaluates
to 4096 on Linux because the guard requires __APPLE__. mprotect()
returns EINVAL at startup and every swift / swiftc / SwiftPM
invocation emits:

    swift runtime: unable to protect path to swift-backtrace at 0x...;
    disabling backtracing.
    swift runtime: unable to protect environment for swift-backtrace
    at 0x...; disabling backtracing.

Over-aligning the static buffers to 16KB on a 4KB-page kernel is safe
(mprotect accepts any multiple of the runtime page size); under-
aligning to 4KB on a 16KB-page kernel is what produces the EINVAL.

Forum thread (Houghton, Swift runtime maintainer, identifying the
same root cause for Raspberry Pi OS):
https://forums.swift.org/t/steps-to-resolve-unable-to-protect-swift-backtrace-disabling-backtracing/72076

---
 swift/include/swift/Runtime/Config.h | 9 ++++++++-
 1 file changed, 8 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/swift/include/swift/Runtime/Config.h
+++ b/swift/include/swift/Runtime/Config.h
@@ -585,10 +585,17 @@
 #endif

 /// What is the system page size?
-#if defined(__APPLE__) && defined(__arm64__)
+#if (defined(__APPLE__) && defined(__arm64__)) || \
+    (defined(__linux__) && defined(__aarch64__))
   // Apple Silicon systems use a 16KB page size
+  //
+  // Also: aarch64 Linux on 16KB-page kernels (Asahi-Linux on Apple
+  // Silicon, Raspberry Pi OS 64-bit, RHEL 9 arm64). Backtrace.cpp's
+  // mprotect() requires the static buffers' alignment to match the
+  // runtime page size. Over-aligning to 16KB is safe on a 4KB-page
+  // kernel; under-aligning to 4KB EINVALs on a 16KB-page kernel.
   #define SWIFT_PAGE_SIZE 16384
 #else
   // Everything else uses 4KB pages
   #define SWIFT_PAGE_SIZE 4096
 #endif
